@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@{u}@{fg shine}Introduction@{uu}@{fg text}

Since a long time, I has the idea to build a HTML pagemaker. I saw other tools
running under other plateforms, like TkHML, or recently WebMagic.

The idea to make HTML pages only with a text editor like vi, emacs could be possible
with macros which insert HTML tags. It's the case for HTML-Heaven. It was my first
idea. But under Amiga, with a so-easy-to-use environment so drag&drop, with powerfull
MUI GUI, WebMaker should be respect this builder spirit.

All products are registered to their authors.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@{u}@{fg shine}Installation@{uu}@{fg text}


WebMaker need to work fine : 
- textfield.gadget (also avail on aminet dev/gui)  
- MUI 3.x+
- AmigaOS 3.x+  - images datatypes gif, etc...

Click on icon to start...

WebMaker is looking for its localization, the drawer progdir:catalogs/your_language
.

WebMaker need the drawer prodir:images
@endnode

@node "Utilisation" "The Way to Use"
@{u}@{fg shine}Using@{uu}@{fg text}

After running, WebMaker opens an text-edit window. Hit your text and drog icons.

You want set a bit of text in bold, for example. Select the text and click under B
gadget, or go to menus.

The main idea is the insert tags into buffer happens where the cursor is. The text
style attributes must be done on selected text.

The use is very intuitive.

All cut-copy-paste functions are enabled.

@endnode

